==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Scammony
<hw>Scam"mo*ny</hw> <pr>(sk⟦acr⟧m"m⟦osl⟧*n⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[F. <ets>scammon⟦eacute⟧e</ets>, L. <ets>scammonia</ets>,
<ets>scammonea</ets>, Gr. <grk>skammwni`a</grk>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A species of bindweed or <gen>Convolvulus</gen>
(<spn>Convolvulus Scammonia</spn>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An inspissated sap obtained from the root of the
<spn>Convolvulus Scammonia</spn>, of a blackish gray color, a nauseous
smell like that of old cheese, and a somewhat acrid taste. It is used in
medicine as a cathartic.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scamp</ent>⟦br⟧
